<br>
explain to me again why they need to be able to tank?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
That's as silly as asking why warriors need to be able to taunt.<br>
<br>
<br>
For a start monks <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>don't</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> need to be able to 'tank'.<br>
It's a mis-conception that in most case monks were ever better 'tanks'.<br>
<br>
Monks did often (with good enough gear) deal with damage better, but that does not always or even mostly equal to tanking better (it <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>did</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>sometimes</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> however), <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>especially</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> not with PoP.<br>
<br>
If dealing with damage was all there was to tanking a SK or Pally would <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NEVER</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be taken as a main tank over a warrior.<br>
Yet sadly this in far from the case.<br>
<br>
Hit points, ability to gain and keep agro, taunt and the steakiness of avoidance compard to mitigation all need to be calculated for tanking.  Not just ability to deal with damage.<br>
<br>
<br>
So your question should be:<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>explain to me again why they need to be able to mitigate?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well think about it, barring tradeskilling when does a melee toon <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NOT</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> need to mitigate?<br>
<br>
Monks need mitigation when pulling (especially when much avoidance does not work from behind and max hits often stun).<br>
<br>
Monks need mitigation when dealing damage anywhere but from behind (and if monks HAVE to be behind then why aren't they doing damage like rogue and if they were that would effectively make rogues useless).<br>
<br>
Monks need mitigation (or at least an increase in avoidance) when soloing.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Do monks need to mitigate as well as warriors?    Possibly not.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>However BREAKING monks does <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">not</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> FIX warriors.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
That is beyond refute, fixing warriors will fix warriors no more no less. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior>The Steel Warrior</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern>The Tavern</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.steelwarrior.org">The Steel Warrior website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
